#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x151
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=263
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@151"
msgid "<Bold>Matter Printers</> can convert raw materials into more complex items ready to be used in further production chains.\r\n\r\nUse the <Bold>connect</> function to automatically feed the output of your <Bold>smelters</> into matter printers to speed up production."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x2fb
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=165
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@2fb"
msgid "The <Bold>Artifact Analyzer</> is now available.\r\n\r\nFeed any <Bold>Alien Artifacts</> you may find into this unit to unlock important new technologies and upgrades."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x3d3
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=109
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@3d3"
msgid "You can now construct <Bold>Fabricators</> in order to produce more complex items and simple starship parts."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x473
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=125
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@473"
msgid "<Bold>Energy Storage</> modules will store excess energy produced by your station ready to restore energy if you lose power."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x586
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=268
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@586"
msgid "You can now automate raw material extraction by constructing <Bold>Miners</> onto <Bold>Ore Nodes</> located on some larger asteroids.\r\n\r\nMiners have <Bold>connection points</> which can be <Bold>built on</> to create mining sub-stations that serve your main station."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x6c5
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=138
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@6c5"
msgid "The <Bold>Small Shipyard</> has now been unlocked.\r\n\r\nSmaller starships can be constructed here to satisfy orders for <Bold>starships</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x7e0
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=276
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@7e0"
msgid "Construct <Bold>Freighter Docks</> to connect remote parts of your station such as miners and further automate resource processing.\r\n\r\n<Bold>Freighters</> can be built from any freighter dock and can then be ordered to pick up and drop off from any docks in the current zone."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x927
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=192
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@927"
msgid "<Bold>Defence Turrets</> can be constructed around your station (and remote sub-stations) to automatically defend from incoming <Bold>meteors</>, <Bold>enemy drones</> and <Bold>creatures</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0xaae
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=343
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@aae"
msgid "You now have access to <Bold>Hydrogen production</> which is used in fusion reactors and starship fuel.\r\n\r\n<Bold>Refineries</> can convert <Bold>water</> from <Bold>ice asteroids</> into <Bold>hydrogen gas</>, which can then be piped around your station and either stored or used in <Bold>Fusion Reactors</> to produce large amounts of power."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0xc38
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=165
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@c38"
msgid "<Bold>Power Linkers</> can be built to link the power grids of remote parts of your station - such as Miners - to your main station and centralize power generation."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0xdb3
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=235
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@db3"
msgid "Additional <Bold>locations</> are now available to you to found new stations at. These can be accessed from the <Bold>System Map</>.\r\n\r\nMore locations will become available as your station grows, allowing access to new resource types."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0xed1
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=168
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@ed1"
msgid "Stations in other locations can be connected together via <Bold>Womhole Terminus</>, which allows movement of items, parts and volatiles between zones to be automated."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0xfac
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=209
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@fac"
msgid "You may now receive orders for starships that have been <Fuelled>Fuelled</>.\r\n\r\nYou can <Fuelled>fuel</> a starship by dragging it into a <Bold>Fuel Depot</> that has been supplied with <Bold>Hydrogen Gas</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x10b0
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=373
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@10b0"
msgid "<Bold>Tug Bays</> will automatically move starships between station modules - such as from a <Bold>Shipyard</> into a <Bold>Fuel Depot</> - or into a <Bold>clear space</> next to your station ready to be shipped.\r\n\r\nUse the <Bold>Connect</> function to assign a Shipyard to a Fuel Depot or a space near your station and the nearest free tug will automatically be assigned."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1258
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=305
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1258"
msgid "<Bold>Cloud Mining Stations</> let you deploy <Bold>Cloud Miners</> into the atmosphere of a gas giant and automate the collection of large amounts of hydrogen gas.\r\n\r\nConstruct <Bold>Vortex generators</> inside the atmosphere of <Bold>Gas giants</> to produce large amounts of power at very little cost."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x13bc
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=264
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@13bc"
msgid "You can now synthesize the highly explosive bio-compound <Bold>Nitrox</>, which can be produced by refining the <Bold>Nitratium</> recovered from gas-giant flora and fauna and combining it in a <Bold>Refinery</> with <Bold>Oxygen</> extracted from <Bold>Water</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x159f
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=170
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@159f"
msgid "Additional mining locations are now available, which give access to new resources - such as the rare metal <Bold>Tungsten</> which is used to create <Bold>Superalloy</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x167c
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=121
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@167c"
msgid "The <Bold>Plasma Forge</> has now been unlocked. Use this to combine elements together to form advanced <Bold>alloys</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1728
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=176
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1728"
msgid "The <Bold>Bio Extractor</> can be used to automate the extraction of <Bold>Nitratium</> from large gas-giant flora in order to automate large-scale <Bold>Nitrox</> production."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x18aa
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=96
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@18aa"
msgid "<Bold>Manufactories</> can now be constructed, allowing the most complex parts to be assembled."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x193d
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=284
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@193d"
msgid "<Bold>Medium Shipyards</> are now available for you to fulfil ever-larger and more complex starship orders.\r\n\r\nNote: Larger ships may require <Bold>Micro Fusion Reactors</> to be installed. These ships must be fuelled quickly after completion to avoid catasptrophic reactor meltdown."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1a8c
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=146
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1a8c"
msgid "The <Bold>Glacialis Ice Ring</> is the ideal location to automate the mining of larger <Bold>Ice Asteroids</> used in <Bold>Oxygen</> production."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1b51
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=153
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1b51"
msgid "We also recommend building enhanced <Bold>Missile Defence Turrets</> on your most vulnerable stations to safely defend against larger groups of enemies."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1ceb
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=230
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1ceb"
msgid "You may now receive orders for <Armed>Military Starships</> which need to be supplied with <Armed>ammunition</>.\r\n\r\n<Armed>Ship Ammo</> is produced in the <Bold>Ammo Factory</> and loaded into a ship from the <Bold>Ammo Depot</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1ed4
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=221
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1ed4"
msgid "The <Bold>Junkyard</> zone has been unlocked. \r\n\r\nThis is a very dangerous sector of space swept by frequent firestorms, so you may want to construct <Bold>Force-Field Generators</> to protect your stations in this area."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x1fe4
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=329
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@1fe4"
msgid "You now have access to <Bold>antimatter</> production - an incredibly powerful force which can be used to generate huge amounts of energy - or to create weapons of mass destruction.\r\n\r\nAntimatter is extremely unstable and must be stored in a powered <Bold>Containment Chamber</> - or it will <bold>explode</> after a short time."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x2160
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=343
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@2160"
msgid "Antimatter is generated inside the <Bold>Particle Accelerator</>. This is formed from a <Bold>Control Centre</> and a ring of <Bold>Conduit</> running through one or more <Bold>Towers</>.\r\n\r\nThe <Bold>larger</> the particle accelerator loop you build, the <Bold>faster</> you can generate antimatter - but the <Bold>more power</> is required."
msgstr ""

#: DT_StationLevel export[0] offset=0x231e
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=305
msgctxt "DT_StationLevel@e0@231e"
msgid "The <Bold>Servitor Station</> deploys a helpful <Bold>AI-powered robot</> that can be set to automatically perform tasks around your station such as <Bold>repairing damaged modules</>, aligning <Bold>solar panels</> and <Bold>collecting resources</> when <Bold>linked</> to a suitable destination module."
msgstr ""

